  "rawMarkdown" : "---\nsource: https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/SerialDriverKit\/PD_RS232_PARITY_MARK\ncrawled: 2026-03-10T21:52:18Z\n---\n\n# PD_RS232_PARITY_MARK\n\n**Macro**\n\nThe mark state.\n\n## Declaration\n\n```swift\n#define PD_RS232_PARITY_MARK\n```\n\n## Discussion\n\nThis value corresponds to placing a logical `1` on the communication line.\n\n## Parity Options\n\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_DEFAULT**: The default parity setting.\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_NONE**: No parity bit.\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_ODD**: An odd parity bit.\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_EVEN**: An even parity bit.\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_SPACE**: The space state.\n- **PD_RS232_PARITY_ANY**: Discard the parity bit.\n\n",
